text: Great news. Israel has indefinitely delayed the demolition of the Bedouin village of Khan al-Ahmar. https://t.co/oBbSX7EVVA

New research shows that many women with breast cancer can safely avoid side effects of chemotherapy without lowering survival rates. Glad to see this research was initially funded by the Breast Cancer Research Stamp a great way to support #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth.
California, today’s your last day to register to vote in November. Make sure your voice counts on Election Day. You can fill out the necessary form here: https://t.co/oeLo9WugwC
Congrats to the @Dodgers, headed back to the #WorldSeries for the 2nd straight year! Do California proud and bring it home! #LADetermined

This is why nearly 70% of Californians oppose offshore drilling. Congress should act quickly to pass the West Coast Ocean Protection Act, our bill to ban drilling along the Pacific coast.  It’s not IF an oil spill will happen, but WHEN. https://t.co/MUjpdLheBi

24,000 American women are diagnosed with breast cancer every year. That’s why we keep fighting for more research. We’ve seen treatment come a long way in the 20 years since we established the Breast Cancer Research Stamp. Lower your risk and get screened. https://t.co/w3fbq5zpOW

“Despite mounting evidence that Mr. Khashoggi, a peaceful critic of the Saudi government, was tortured and killed, the White House has continued to equivocate on the obvious and coddled Saudi leaders. Proud to join @SenKamalaHarris in a #WorldSeries wager against @SenWarren and @SenMarkey. Dodger Dogs and LA’s famous guacamole against Boston clam chowder. Let’s go @Dodgers! #LADetermined

Sandra Day O’Connor is a legend. A 40-year career in public service that included 25 historic years on the Supreme Court. She is a trailblazer and a model for us all. I wish her all my best as she faces this latest challenge.

Leaders have a responsibility to calm tensions, not inflame them. I urge everyone to be vigilant in the face of threats and thank all the law enforcement personnel who are protecting government and private sites from attack.

More than 900,000 lbs. of prescription drugs have been taken off our streets this year thanks to programs like National Take Back Day. Do your part on October 27, visit https://t.co/qZM5b1pyzK for more info and to find take back locations near you. #DEATakeBack

This is what climate change looks like: Northern California has lost 93% of its underwater kelp forests in just five years. A marine heatwave helped trigger a population boom for purple urchins, which devoured the kelp. https://t.co/1bSLKHOVRd

Happy 73rd anniversary to the UN! The UN is an important venue to promote peace and cooperation worldwide. This is a great time to look back at everything the UN has accomplished and recommit ourselves to the its goals. https://t.co/rYdKgjALtI

My thoughts are with our fellow countrymen in the Northern Mariana Islands who are just beginning a long road to recovery after Super Typhoon Yutu. Please stay safe, we will be here to help in the aftermath of this massive storm.

In 2016, 6.2 million Americans misused prescription drugs. Prevent your prescription drugs from becoming part of the opioid crisis. Saturday is National Prescription Drug Take Back Day. Visit https://t.co/qZM5b1pyzK for locations near you. #DEATakeBack

20 years after a vicious hate crime took his life, Matthew Shepard continues to inspire LGBT youth to live their authentic lives. I can think of no more fitting tribute to his life than his burial at the National Cathedral.

If it weren’t for President Trump and the GOP’s sabotage of the Affordable Care Act, premiums would be 16% lower than they are today. Reintroducing junk plans and gutting the individual mandate are only serving to make health care more expensive. https://t.co/FHCk7c0XK3
Happy Navy Day to all who have served. What a great way to round out Fleet Week in San Diego this weekend. Be sure to thank the service members in your life for their sacrifice.

I’m heartbroken by the tragic shooting at the Tree of Life Synagogue in Pittsburgh. This is an act of hate, plain & simple. Hatred & easy access to assault weapons has left at least 11 dead & four police officers wounded. Only we let civilians so easily access weapons of war.

Strong fuel-emissions standards save consumers money on gas, grow jobs in auto manufacturing and fuel-efficient technologies, and help the American auto industry compete internationally. The Trump administration’s proposal to freeze them makes no sense. https://t.co/dDMSPIZC6X

As open enrollment continues, it’s important to remember that California has seen great improvements in coverage as a result of the Affordable Care Act.  We’ve gone from a state with 16% uninsured in 2013 to 7% today.
Proud of the @Dodgers and their hard-fought season. Thanks for taking California back to the World Series! #LADetermined

Happy 40th birthday to the San Francisco Gay Men’s Chorus! It’s been a pleasure to see it grow from Jon Reed Sims’ gathering of 100 to the institution it is today. I can’t wait to see what you do in the years to come. @sfgmc

These immigrants are only seeking a fair chance to make their case. They’d be following the law—not breaking it—if they present themselves at a port of entry requesting asylum. Giving the world’s most vulnerable people the opportunity for a better life is a bedrock American value https://t.co/mwaALuWyOM

Great to see the FDA bar the use of lead acetate. This is an ingredient in some men’s hair dyes and exposure may be harmful. While this is a good first step, lead acetate is just one of many ingredients in personal care products that needs further safety evaluation.

New science shows the oceans are warming more than we thought. We may have to cut emissions 25% faster to avoid a disastrous 2°C of global warming. It’s time to stop pretending climate change isn’t a real threat—our future depends on it. https://t.co/Lj6ECyMr54

We must make sure the Violence Against Women Act has meaningful improvements that address the needs of victims and survivors. Women are speaking out about sexual harassment and assault like never before and they’re done tolerating the status quo. https://t.co/raBV0XR6Oo

There’s a reason the @Giants give the Willie Mac Award to the most inspirational players and home run balls land in McCovey Cove—Willie McCovey was the heart of the team for 19 years and one of its most beloved players. He’ll be greatly missed.

8,300 children are sent to emergency rooms with gunshot wounds every year. It’s clear the public health risk of guns needs to be studied. We already lifted the prohibition on CDC studying gun violence, now let’s actually fund a study. https://t.co/GAgGmo3UOR

We can’t help homeless children and youth without knowing how many are homeless and why they are homeless. Reports like this one lead to a more accurate count of America’s homeless youth, which is crucial to getting them housed. https://t.co/r1eDADMyj6

On average Latinas are paid 53 cents for every dollar earned by white men. And in California specifically, it drops to 43 cents. That’s appalling. We won’t settle for anything less than equal pay for equal work. #LatinaEqualPayDay

The president is stoking fear about immigrants seeking asylum to score cheap political points. These families are fleeing violence in search of a better life. They are not an urgent national security threat.  https://t.co/BB4rDqSDlc

New numbers from HUD show a drop in homeless veterans in both California and across the nation. While this is encouraging news, we have much more work ahead of us. It will take all of us working together to end homelessness. https://t.co/7BAXkHYetM

President Trump continues to disparage immigrants seeking asylum with no evidence for his claims. These immigrants are mostly women and children. They'd be following the law—not breaking it—if they present themselves at a port of entry requesting asylum. https://t.co/BB4rDqSDlc

As we head into Shabbat we stand together against anti-Semitism across the country. It’s a testament to what we have in common that so many people of different faiths are coming together to support the Jewish community after last week’s attack. #ShowUpForShabbat

Today is the day! Get out and cast your ballot, voting is fundamental to our democracy. If you don’t know where your polling place is, find it here: https://t.co/fRcesko8o8

Facts are facts: before the Affordable Care Act, 16% of Californians were uninsured, today it’s 7%. We’re still working to ensure everyone has affordable, quality health insurance but there’s no denying we’ve made incredible progress despite repeated attempts to repeal the ACA.

Harmful actions like expanding narrow and limited health care plans, a lawsuit to end protections for preexisting conditions, higher premiums, multiple votes on the Senate floor and now promises to pursue repeal again, that’s the Republican record on health care. Period.
Members of our military and their families sacrifice greatly to keep our nation safe. The very least we can do in return is ensure their housing is safe and sanitary. https://t.co/jb3qbJdpFJ

The president has made abundantly clear that he’ll take any action he can to undermine the Mueller investigation. Heartbroken to hear about the shooting in Thousand Oaks. I’m closely following developments. There is a Family Assistance and Reunification Center at 1375 E. Janss Rd in Thousand Oaks for those with loved ones involved as well as an emergency hotline (805) 465-6650.

My thoughts are with all those affected by the fires burning across the state. Please heed any evacuation orders in your area. You can find information from @CAL_FIRE on all major fires and current evacuation orders here: https://t.co/4CHELHv0rX
Heartbroken to hear about the deaths in California from these latest fires. PLEASE follow all @CAL_FIRE evacuation orders closely. Learn more here: https://t.co/4CHELHv0rX

Happy 243rd birthday to the Marine Corps! I hope all Marines around the globe enjoy a well-deserved celebration.

Federal funds are available right now to help wildfire victims with immediate needs. Those affected should register with FEMA as soon as possible online at https://t.co/gtwgF2rX1M or by calling 800-621-3362 or 800-462-7585 TTY.
If you’ve been forced to evacuate your home, locate an emergency shelter near you by texting “SHELTER” and your zip code to 43362 or calling 201 for information on local resources.
You can find the current status of evacuations here: https://t.co/4CHELHdp3n. Please review @CAL_FIRE’s latest information before deciding to return to your home.
If you’re returning to your homes after evacuation, please follow @CAL_FIRE’s guidelines for navigating your way back and what to do when you arrive. https://t.co/naN4Zs9INE

A Butte County Disaster Recovery Center is open. The center is located in the former Sears store at the Chico Mall, 1982 East 20th Street. The center will be open seven days a week from 9 a.m. to 7 p.m.

A Local Assistance Center is open in Thousand Oaks at the Grant R. Brimhall Library, 1401 E. Janss Road. The center is open until Tuesday, Nov. 20, from 9 a.m. to 7 p.m. on weekdays and 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. on weekends. To request transportation call 805-375-5467.

Eligible blood and platelet donors are encouraged to schedule an appointment to give by using the Blood Donor App, visiting https://t.co/8gVeCzkQIP or calling 800-RED CROSS (800-733-2767). Every little bit helps as we try to help wildfire victims.

To apply for FEMA wildfire assistance you’ll need several documents including:
 
Social Security number
Insurance coverage information
Bank account and routing numbers
 
If you have lost documents in the fire, contact my office at 415-393-0707 for assistance requesting new ones.
